>I'm also uncomfortable with what I understand to be David's claim that
>there was some historical justification for the "paranoia" that led to
>gross excesses of domestic political surveillance. I'm not convinced
>that starting a "Red Squad File" on somebody for belonging to the
>National Lawyer's Guild or writing a letter in opposition to the Viet Nam
>war are so-easily justified. That David Sternlight can suggest that
>such acts "were not unjustified on the historical record" only reinforces
>the need to oppose Clipper lest a similar "historical record" emerges
